Well, if you're going to stick to JVM properties passed from the environment for now, you might as well look for and use http.proxyUser and http.proxyPassword. There's an alternative `Proxy` constructor that takes an extra `Authentication` argument. I confess I'm a bit confused by the abstractions in aether, but I _think_ you could substitute the first return statement in your `AetherGrapeEngine.defaultProxy` method with something like this:

```
            String proxyUser = System.getProperty("http.proxyUser");
            String proxyPassword = System.getProperty("http.proxyPassword");
            if ((proxyUser != null) && (proxyPassword != null)) {
                AuthenticationBuilder auth = new AuthenticationBuilder();
                auth.addUsername(proxyUser).addPassword(proxyPassword);
                return new Proxy("http", proxyHost, new Integer(
                        System.getProperty("http.proxyPort", "80")),
                        auth.build());
            } else {
                return new Proxy("http", proxyHost, new Integer(
                        System.getProperty("http.proxyPort", "80")));
            }
```

